From: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PEGTL: fix demangle() static_assert with GCC 16

The bundled PEGTL parses __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ at compile time to demangle
type names. Older GCC emits

  ...[with T = X; std::string_view = std::basic_string_view<char>]

so the code locates the end of the type name via rfind(';'). GCC 16 no
longer emits the trailing "; std::string_view = ..." alias and produces

  ...[with T = X]

which makes rfind(';') return npos and trips:

  src/ThirdParty/PEGTL/include/tao/pegtl/demangle.hpp:118:23:
  error: static assertion failed

Fall back to the closing ']' when no ';' is present so both old and new
GCC __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ layouts work.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>
---
 src/ThirdParty/PEGTL/include/tao/pegtl/demangle.hpp | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/ThirdParty/PEGTL/include/tao/pegtl/demangle.hpp
+++ b/src/ThirdParty/PEGTL/include/tao/pegtl/demangle.hpp
@@ -114,7 +114,11 @@
    constexpr auto begin = sv.find( '=' );
    static_assert( begin != std::string_view::npos );
    constexpr auto tmp = sv.substr( begin + 2 );
-   constexpr auto end = tmp.rfind( ';' );
+   // Older GCC emits "...[with T = X; std::string_view = ...]", newer GCC
+   // (16+) drops the trailing "; std::string_view = ..." alias and emits
+   // "...[with T = X]". Cope with both by falling back to the closing ']'.
+   constexpr auto semi = tmp.rfind( ';' );
+   constexpr auto end = ( semi != std::string_view::npos ) ? semi : tmp.rfind( ']' );
    static_assert( end != std::string_view::npos );
    return tmp.substr( 0, end );
 }
